Limbic System: *Beeaautiful*... Believe me, stupid ape, its lack of beauty was *not* the problem.

You: Yes, that.
Ancient Reptilian Brain: Don't prod at it, it will start moving again.
Ancient Reptilian Brain: Again.

You: Enough... just lie there, motionless.
Ancient Reptilian Brain: You think they would let you -- until you disintegrate into biomolecules? No, someone is breathing on your face now, inspecting your pupils. Stupid idiot.
You: I'm not coming back...
You: What is that? It's cold...

You: ...where am I?
Ancient Reptilian Brain: Your name is *fuck all*.
Limbic System: It certainly ain't Harry.
Ancient Reptilian Brain: Well, *almost* nothing. There is the ground below you. That's still there. And the small light that's on -- fluttering -- somewhere in the Basal Ganglia.
You: Who's that?
Ancient Reptilian Brain: Is it? The world is gone, you're no longer reacting to outward stimuli. Yet still...
Limbic System: Here in the Paleo-Mammalian Cortex we call it -- *the shadow*.
Limbic System: Oh, but you are. They're pouring something on you, *in* you. It's...
Ancient Reptilian Brain: Yeah, man, what was that about?
Coupris Kineema: The water is cold, silvery -- the stuff of *life itself* as it pours down your parched throat. The pounding in your head recedes, the darkness parts.
You: "Let's solve this case." [Leave.]
Kim Kitsuragi: "What happened?"
finale_for_fiasco
Kim Kitsuragi: "That does sometimes happen." He hands you the remains of your ledger.
Rhetoric: He replies with such understanding it's as if the burnt out ruins of the past were an occupational hazard -- athlete's foot for cops.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Right." he hands you the waterlogged remains of your ledger.
Kim Kitsuragi: "But these are not the *Franconigerian centuries*. We are in the present. It is safe to sometimes drink water here." He hands you the canister.

You: "How long was I out?"
Ancient Reptilian Brain: That's me, blue eyes. That's me.
You: Nice and quiet.

You: Drink.
You: "No. I don't wanna."
You: "You know, in the Franconigerian centuries, the quality of water was so bad it was sometimes more hygienic to drink beer."
You: "I came in contact with the burnt out ruins of the past, lieutenant." (Conclude.)
Ancient Reptilian Brain: Nothing, sad brother. No treachery. Just blackout.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Good." He hands you the waterlogged remains of your ledger.
Kim Kitsuragi: "Drink -- water." The lieutenant is extending a small canister to your mouth.
You: Was that the ex-something? The...
You: Where is Voyager Road?
Ancient Reptilian Brain: There is no Voyager Road. There are no roads. No houses. No lights in the windows. It's all on *pause*.
You: "I... fuck it." Start climbing out of the motor-car. (Conclude.)
You: "I was dehydrated. It won't happen again." (Conclude.)
Kim Kitsuragi: "You were reading your paperwork. Then you passed out. I carried you to my Kineema... to take you to a hospital. Then you came to."
You: So my name appears to be... Harry?
Kim Kitsuragi: "Ten minutes maybe."
You: Smelled like betrayal.
Ancient Reptilian Brain: Yeah, man. Fuck *everything*. Total blackout forever.
Limbic System: He speaks of the *sickening* longing, the unwell emotion. Even in the darkness he's grasping for it, still trying to hold on to the great sorrows slipping in the water -- slimy.
You: Yeah, that's the stuff!
You: No, I was *cool*. I'm cool.
Volition: There really *is* no use arguing with him. This is him exerting the reserves of authority he usually withholds. You can't even try to resist. All you can do is...

You: Smelled so nice...
Kim Kitsuragi: "That's just a drug addict myth. In reality you're still comprised of dihydrogen oxide, which you must replenish to go on living."
You: Drink.

Coupris Kineema: In the upholstered cabin of Lieutenant Kitsuragi's motor carriage, seated in the driver's basket. The air is thick with leatherworks and heavy fuel oil. Cold water runs down your chin.
You: "You know, I'm actually more of a *magnesium* based lifeform now."
Jump to: [Kim Kitsuragi: ""What happened?""]
Limbic System: Your name is *Passed Out on the Ground*. Dragged around by one of the other evil apes. They're taking you somewhere...
You: Then what is it?
Rhetoric: Actually, beer and cider have *loads* of water in them.
Kim Kitsuragi: "I found this next to you." He pauses. "I'll tag along for the rest of the day if you don't mind. My business is concluded anyway. Are you okay to go?"
Limbic System: Yes, they're *pouring* something on you -- something *in* you. And it's...
Kim Kitsuragi: "Drink." He tilts the canister. "You haven't drunk water in two days. Did you know the human body is not made to survive on alcohol *alone*? You need a secondary form of hydration."
